{"indexed":{"date-parts":[[2023,7,26]],"date-time":"2023-07-26T17:11:21Z","timestamp":1690391481161},"reference-count":14,"publisher":"Pensoft Publishers","license":[{"start":{"date-parts":[[2022,10,26]],"date-time":"2022-10-26T00:00:00Z","timestamp":1666742400000},"content-version":"vor","delay-in-days":0,"URL":"http:\/\/creativecommons.org\/licenses\/by\/4.0\/"}],"content-domain":{"domain":[],"crossmark-restriction":false},"abstract":"<jats:p>We describe three new species of the previously monotypic genus <jats:italic>Creagrura<\/jats:italic> Townes from Central and South America: <jats:italic>C. alejandromasisi<\/jats:italic> <jats:bold>sp. n.<\/jats:bold> and <jats:italic>C. rogerblancoi<\/jats:italic> <jats:bold>sp. n.<\/jats:bold> from Costa Rica and <jats:italic>C. allpahuaya<\/jats:italic> <jats:bold>sp. n.<\/jats:bold> from Peru, all of which emphasise the unknown parasitoid insect diversity yet to be revealed in the tropics.<\/jats:p>\n          <jats:p>Host relationships of the two Costa Rican species are described in detail. In addition, it is inferred that the <jats:italic>Creagrura<\/jats:italic> wasps find and oviposit in the caterpillar when it is exposed at night, rather than when it is concealed during daylight hours.<\/jats:p>","DOI":"10.3897\/bdj.10.e91486","type":"journal-article","created":{"date-parts":[[2022,10,26]],"date-time":"2022-10-26T09:50:45Z","timestamp":1666777845000},"source":"Crossref","is-referenced-by-count":1,"title":"Cryptic biodiversity of tropical hesperiid caterpillar-attacking parasitoid wasps: three new species of Creagrura Townes (Hymenoptera, Ichneumonidae, Cremastinae) from Costa Rica and Per\u00fa","prefix":"10.3897","volume":"10","author":[{"given":"Ilari","family":"S\u00e4\u00e4ksj\u00e4rvi","sequence":"first","affiliation":[]},{"ORCID":"http:\/\/orcid.org\/0000-0001-6665-0047","authenticated-orcid":true,"given":"Kari","family":"Kaunisto","sequence":"additional","affiliation":[]},{"ORCID":"http:\/\/orcid.org\/0000-00